    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp] </span><strong>flour</strong> and stir with a wooden spoon for 1-2 min</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potato</strong>, <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>carrot</strong> and <strong>chicken stock </strong>to the pot and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook, covered, for 18-20 min or until the carrot and potato are fork-tender, stirring occasionally</p>",
